<div class="top-part">
  <%= render 'shared/navbar' %>

  <h1>🦄Press ONE random key🦄</h1>
  
  <div class="info-box">
    <p class="p-info">The key you pressed is the <strong>root</strong>, and the two keys suggested to you are called a “<strong>major third</strong>” and a “<strong>perfect fifth</strong>”.</p>
    <p class="p-info">Together, those three make up a <strong>major triad</strong>, it is one of the building blocks of tonal music in western pop, folk and rock music.</p>
    <p class="p-info">It sounds <strong>constant and stable</strong>.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="open-btn">
    <button id="open">
      See how this chord is used in a real composition
    </button>
  </div>

  <div>
    <%= render 'shared/piano' %>
  </div>
</div>

